First of all i wanna thank you for your answers. In
order to explain why i need to do that in my case is
the following: The aim of our bachelor-project was to
develop a web-application with which you can analyze
web-pages with the long term goal to achieve better
rankings in common Web-search-Engines (Google,
Altavista, Yahoo...) without having to use spammer
techniques (150 meta-tags...). The result of the
project (it&#39;s almost finished, just some things
missing e.g. user-agent) is that you are able to write
custom &quot;checks&quot; (e.g. you check the crawled pages for
the size, or you go through the first 100 words of the
page and count the number of occurences of a
pre-defined word...), hook it up to the custom
processor i developed and have the crawler check each
URI against the desired checks for this crawl. (Btw.
the whole project is NOT designed for public use so in
my eyes it&#39;s ok to change the user-agent) 
