&gt; I will just like to add on to the Stack&#39;s note.
&gt; These days webmasters pay close attention to Web
&gt; crawlers. If you pose to be googlebot it is most 
&gt; likely that IP addresses or entire IP range that you
&gt; are using for crawling will be blocked from 
&gt; many sites. This will indefinitely prevent you from
&gt; crawling these sites in future.
&gt; On the other hand, there are many sites out there
&gt; (a.k.a cloakers) that are trying to trick Google 
&gt; and other search-engine crawlers to get better
&gt; ranking. In this case you will be crawling a lot 
&gt; &quot;junk&quot; that these cloakers server to popular
&gt; crawlers...All in all, I strongly recommend not to
&gt; pose 
&gt; as other popular crawlers since it will cause you
&gt; more trouble than good. As Stack suggested you 
&gt; should work on creating good relationships with
&gt; webmasters. Keep in mind that in crawling business 
&gt; it is easy to get bad reputation.
